		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hello all,<br /><br />I run a windows 7 - 64bit computer and I'm only able to run a select few of the programs I find for NES graphics editing. I was wondering if someone could steer me into the right direction. Currently I have a bmp file with 4 different colors in it. Although I'm sure they are not all NES compatible I assumed that when pasting them into YYCHR it would recognize  it as 4 different colors. When pasting I'm seeing it past it has white and black? Is there a set of instructions out there that shows me how to use YYCHR with intentions of developing graphics for a homebrew rather than editing roms graphics? <br /><br />Also to give a better background to what I'm trying to do... I'm trying to take this BPM image and have it as a background in my &quot;game&quot; (I'd like to make a one screen greetings card really). Is there any tutorial out there that shows how to create backgrounds for games from scratch? Load a chr and set it as the background (or however you do it)? Also keep in mind I'd like to do this in C as I'm not familiar with assembly. <br /><br /><br />Thanks,<br />Jake<br /><br />P.S any graphics tutorials you know of that are NOT related to rom editing please send my way <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

		

